title: Wimbledon 2009 - Mens Final - Day 13 (5th July 2009)
description:
Wimbledon 2009 - Mens Final - Day 13 (5th July 2009) 

Sunday 5th July 2009
1:30pm - 7:00pm
BBC1

From a British point of view, the wrong Andy made it through to the final. But Roddick will have his work cut out for him against Roger Federer, who is 

chasing his record-breaking 15th Grand Slam - and his sixth Wimbledon title in seven years. Roddick's huge serve - the fastest ever recorded - is his most 

dangerous weapon and was used to great effect against Andy Murray in the previous round. He's in arguably the best form of his life, too. A win for him would 

still count as an upset, but it's not outside the bounds of possibility.
